            "answer_text": "first of all need to understand what actually a*b is. (* represtants cross product )a*b is the resultant vector which is always perpendicular to the each single vector a & b.means a*b is like z -axis which is perpenducular to each x & y- axes for any x-y-z plane .now a\u2022(a*b) means dot product of vector a & (a*b).we know that if two vectors are perpendicular to each other that means their dot product is always zero i.e. a\u2022b =O .now ,recall point no.2 .since a*b is perpendicular to a & b then a\u2022(a*b) =O as well b\u2022(a*b)=O. ( a*b & a are perpendicular to each other so there dot product is equal to the zero.)",
